Package: rijkspalette
Type: Package
Title: Create Colour Palettes Based on Famous Artworks from the Rijksmuseum
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Erik-Jan van Kesteren
Maintainer: Erik-Jan van Kesteren <e.vankesteren1@uu.nl>
Description: This package creates colour palettes based on paintings of famous
    artists. Using the function rijksPalette(), you can search for and 
    automatically generate a colour palette from any painting in the collection
    of the Dutch Rijksmuseum. This package was developed using the fantastic 
    Rijksmuseum API.
License: MIT + file LICENCE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: imager,
    utils,
    crayon,
    grDevices,
    jsonlite,
    curl
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: manipulate
